Global RISC-V Based SoCs Market Insights
RISC-V Based SoCs Market size was valued at USD 1.72 Billion in 2022 and is projected to reach USD 5.03 Billion by 2030, growing at a CAGR of 18.1% from 2024 to 2030.

RISC-V Based SoCs Market Overview
The RISC-V architecture has emerged as a transformative force in the semiconductor industry, particularly in the development of System-on-Chip (SoC) solutions. In 2023, RISC-V intellectual property (IP) revenues reached $156 million, with projections indicating a compound annual growth rate (CAGR) of 39.5% through 2030. This growth trajectory is driven by the architecture's open-source nature, enabling customization and cost efficiency across various sectors. By 2030, RISC-V-based SoC unit shipments are expected to increase to 16.2 billion units, with revenues reaching $92 billion. The integration of RISC-V in applications such as AI accelerators, FPGAs, and microcontroller units (MCUs) underscores its expanding influence in the market.

